SIMPLE: squab
RECORDS: 4

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Squab
<hw>Squab</hw> <pr>(skw⟦ocr⟧b)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. dial. Sw.
<ets>sqvabb</ets> a soft and fat body, <ets>sqvabba</ets> a fat woman,
Icel. <ets>kvap</ets> jelly, jellylike things, and E.
<ets>quab</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Fat; thick; plump;
bulky.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Nor the <qex>squab</qex> daughter nor the wife were nice.</q>
<rj><qau>Betterton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Unfledged; unfeathered; <as>as, a <ex>squab</ex>
pigeon</as>.</def> <rj><au>King.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Squab</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Squab
<hw>Squab</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
nestling of a pigeon or other similar bird, esp. when very fat and not
fully fledged.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A person of a short, fat figure.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Gorgonious sits abdominous and wan,⟦br⟧
Like a fat <qex>squab</qex> upon a Chinese fan.</q>
<rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A thickly stuffed cushion; especially, one used for
the seat of a sofa, couch, or chair; also, a sofa.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Punching the <qex>squab</qex> of chairs and sofas.</q>
<rj><qau>Dickens.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>On her large <qex>squab</qex> you find her spread.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Squab</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Squab
<hw>Squab</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[Cf. dial. Sw. <ets>sqvapp</ets>, a
word imitative of a splash, and E. <ets>squab</ets> fat,
unfledged.]</ety> <def>With a heavy fall; plump.</def>
<mark>[Vulgar]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The eagle took the tortoise up into the air, and dropped him down,
<qex>squab</qex>, upon a rock.</q> <rj><qau>L'Estrange.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Squab</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Squab
<hw>Squab</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To fall plump; to strike at one
dash, or with a heavy stroke.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Squabash</ent>⟦br⟧
